    {
      "id": "51464938e3b0f4502437b8718ff13ddc7a501413",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-15 00:56:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\nIt's not a bad patch, but makes me wonder whether it is worthwhile to have an autoconf check for something that can be checked directly in the code via:\n\n #ifndef __REQ_WRITE /* before 2.6.35 */\n #define _REQ_WRITE BIO_RW\n #endif\n\nor so?\n\nThe benefit of the autoconf check is that it will be clear when it is time to be cleaned up, but the test will also need to be deleted instead of just one place. In the end it isn't a huge deal either way.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "79a9285781dea2aede7feb0747bbf7e273170cea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 17:06:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHm, whitespace in this patch does not conform to our new standards?\nperhaps that's an opportunity to update the patch and at the same time to incorporate Andreas' suggestion if you see merit in it?\n\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "72e2dfe40f93314db2e961d08ebd089cfb7566fb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 298,
        "name": "Jeff Mahoney",
        "email": "jeffm@suse.com",
        "username": "jeffm"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-19 17:10:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI did the ifndef in my first iteration but figured that autoconf rules were the way of the project. I have zero problem removing it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
